<i>noun</i>: 협정 [협쩡], 협약 [혀뱍], 합치 [합치], 합의점 [하븨쩜/하비쩜], 합의 [하븨/하비], 찬성 [찬ː성], 조응 [조ː응], 일치 [일치], 영합 [영합], 약정서 [약쩡서], 맞장구 [맏짱구], 동조 [동조], 동의 [동의/동이], 동감 [동감], 담합 [담합], 계약 [계ː약/게ː약] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>협정 [협쩡]</dt><br>
<dd>1. agreement; deal</dd><br>
<dd>서로 의논하여 결정함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of making a decision through discussion.</dd><br>
<dd>2. agreement; treaty; pact</dd><br>
<dd>한 국가가 다른 국가와 약정을 맺음. 또는 그 약정.</dd><br>
<dd>A state of making an agreement with another country; or the agreement.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>협약 [혀뱍]</dt><br>
<dd>convention; agreement; treaty</dd><br>
<dd>공동의 목적을 이루기 위해 여러 사람이 의논하여 약속을 맺음. 또는 그 약속.</dd><br>
<dd>A state in which many people reach an agreement through discussion to accomplish a common goal; or the agreement.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>합치 [합치]</dt><br>
<dd>agreement; accord</dd><br>
<dd>의견, 주장, 생각 등이 서로 어긋나지 않고 정확히 맞음.</dd><br>
<dd>A state in which one has exactly the same opinion, view, or thought as another.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>합의점 [하븨쩜/하비쩜]</dt><br>
<dd>agreement; common ground</dd><br>
<dd>서로의 의견이 일치하는 점.</dd><br>
<dd>A point at which two or more people reach an agreement.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>합의 [하븨/하비]</dt><br>
<dd>agreement; consensus</dd><br>
<dd>서로 의견이 일치함. 또는 그 의견.</dd><br>
<dd>A state of having the same opinion as someone else; or such an opinion.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>찬성 [찬ː성]</dt><br>
<dd>agreement; consent</dd><br>
<dd>다른 사람의 의견이나 생각 등이 좋다고 인정해 뜻을 같이함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of acknowledging another person's opinion, idea, etc., as meritorious and endorsing it.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>조응 [조ː응]</dt><br>
<dd>1. agreement</dd><br>
<dd>둘 이상의 사물이나 현상, 말과 글의 앞뒤 등이 서로 알맞게 어울림.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of two or more things, phenomena, words, passages, etc., being in contextual agreement with each other.</dd><br>
<dd>2. result; outcome</dd><br>
<dd>원인에 따른 결과가 생김.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of an effect happening from a cause.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>일치 [일치]</dt><br>
<dd>accord; agreement</dd><br>
<dd>비교되는 대상이 서로 다르지 않고 꼭 같거나 들어맞음.</dd><br>
<dd>A state in which things in comparison are not different, either being exactly the same or matching one another.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>영합 [영합]</dt><br>
<dd>1. flattery; adulation; ingratiation</dd><br>
<dd>개인적인 이익을 위해 마음에 없는 칭찬을 하며 따름.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of praising someone without meaning it, for one's personal gains.</dd><br>
<dd>2. agreement; understanding</dd><br>
<dd>서로 뜻이 맞음.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of being of one mind.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>약정서 [약쩡서]</dt><br>
<dd>agreement; contract</dd><br>
<dd>약속하여 정한 내용을 적은 문서.</dd><br>
<dd>A document that records the details of an agreement or a contract.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>맞장구 [맏짱구]</dt><br>
<dd>1. agreement</dd><br>
<dd>남의 말이 옳다고 호응하거나 동의하는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of agreeing or responding positively to another person's words.</dd><br>
<dd>2. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>둘이 마주 서서 장구를 치는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of two persons facing each other while hitting the janggu, an hourglass-shaped drum, together.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>동조 [동조]</dt><br>
<dd>agreement</dd><br>
<dd>다른 사람의 말이나 생각, 주장 등을 옳게 여겨 따름.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of considering a person's remark, thought, argument, etc., right and following it.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>동의 [동의/동이]</dt><br>
<dd>agreement</dd><br>
<dd>같은 의견.</dd><br>
<dd>The same opinion as another has.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>동감 [동감]</dt><br>
<dd>agreement</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 의견에 같은 생각을 가짐. 또는 그 생각.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of thinking the same as others do, or such a thought.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>담합 [담합]</dt><br>
<dd>1. agreement</dd><br>
<dd>서로 의논하여 의견을 일치시킴.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of discussing and reaching an agreement.</dd><br>
<dd>2. bid rigging</dd><br>
<dd>경쟁 입찰에서 입찰자들이 부당하게 미리 의논하여 입찰 가격을 정함.</dd><br>
<dd>Bidders conspiring to fix bidding prices illegally in a public tender.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>계약 [계ː약/게ː약]</dt><br>
<dd>contract; agreement</dd><br>
<dd>돈을 주고받는 거래에서 서로 지켜야 할 의무나 책임을 문서에 적어 약속함.</dd><br>
<dd>Agreeing on and specifying mutual obligations or accountabilities in a document, in a transaction where money is given or received.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>